# Absolute and Relative URL Project (HTML)

## Project Overview
This project demonstrates the difference between **Absolute URLs** and **Relative URLs** using simple HTML examples. It helps beginners understand how links work in web development.

---

## What are URLs?

### 🔹 Absolute URL
An Absolute URL is the full web address that includes the protocol (https://), domain name, and path.

**Example:**
```html
<a href="https://www.google.com">Go to Google</a>

